description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within Thoracic Surgery at Nottingham University Hospital trust for a 1st level registered nurse who is enthusiastic, motivated and caring to develop their professional knowledge and ability. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Barclay is an 18 bedded Thoracic Surgery Unit and 4 bedded level 2 progressive care unit situated at Nottingham City Hospital. &lt;br /&gt;We are a forward thinking unit with a caring and supportive multidisciplinary team and we pride ourselves on team work, the delivery of high standards of care and patient safety. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a caring and supportive team of nurses dedicated to the delivery of effective patient care. Good communication skills and the ability to work flexibly as part of a team are essential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Personal and professional development is actively supported. There are numerous opportunities for nurses with a keen interest in the development of link nurse roles and we offer opportunities for professional development. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should be educated to 1st level RGN, have excellent verbal and written communication skills. You should be able to prioritise workload and work well as a member of the team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a caring and positive person you will be committed to delivering high quality care whilst adhering to trust values and behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is an internal rotation post and you will be expected to work nights, weekends, bank holidays etc..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name-Lorraine Alexander&lt;/p&gt;
